You can use the [org.json][1] library; it is easy to use.
 
Just remember (while casting or using methods like getJSONObject and getJSONArray) that in JSON notation
[ … ] represents an array, so library will parse it to JSONArray
{ … } represents an object, so library will parse it to JSONObject
 
You can see more [information][1] about.


You can see a simple example below:
 
JSON file:

    {
           &quot;pageInfo&quot;: {
                 &quot;pageName&quot;: &quot;abc&quot;,
                 &quot;pagePic&quot;: &quot;http://example.com/content.jpg&quot;
            },
            &quot;posts&quot;: [
                 {
                      &quot;post_id&quot;: &quot;123456789012_123456789012&quot;,
                      &quot;actor_id&quot;: &quot;1234567890&quot;,
                      &quot;picOfPersonWhoPosted&quot;: &quot;http://example.com/photo.jpg&quot;,
                      &quot;nameOfPersonWhoPosted&quot;: &quot;Jane Doe&quot;,
                      &quot;message&quot;: &quot;Sounds cool. Can&#39;t wait to see it!&quot;,
                      &quot;likesCount&quot;: &quot;2&quot;,
                      &quot;comments&quot;: [],
                      &quot;timeOfPost&quot;: &quot;1234567890&quot;
                 }
            ]
        }

Code example:

    import org.json.*;
    
    String jsonString = ... ; //assign your JSON String here
    JSONObject obj = new JSONObject(jsonString);
    String pageName = obj.getJSONObject(&quot;pageInfo&quot;).getString(&quot;pageName&quot;);
    
    JSONArray arr = obj.getJSONArray(&quot;posts&quot;); // notice that `&quot;posts&quot;: [...]`
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; arr.length(); i++)
    {
        String post_id = arr.getJSONObject(i).getString(&quot;post_id&quot;);
        ......
    }

You may find more examples here: [Parse JSON in Java][2].
 
[Downloadable jar][3].


  [1]: https://github.com/stleary/JSON-java
  [2]: http://theoryapp.com/parse-json-in-java/
  [3]: http://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.json/json

